ArrayDeque
Interview Questions

Q1. What is ArrayDeque in Java?
-->ArrayDeque is a class in the Java Collections Framework that implements the Deque interface. It is a resizable array-based
implementation of a double-ended queue, allowing insertion and deletion of elements from both the front and the rear.
      
      It can be used as both:
      
      Queue (FIFO)
      Stack (LIFO)
      Characteristics
      Implements Deque and Queue.
      Dynamic (resizable) array implementation.
      Allows duplicate elements.
      Does not allow null values.
      Not synchronized.
      Faster than Stack and LinkedList for stack and queue operations.
      
      Example:
      
      import java.util.*;
      
      public class Demo {
          public static void main(String[] args) {
      
              ArrayDeque<String> deque = new ArrayDeque<>();
      
              deque.add("Java");
              deque.add("Python");
              deque.addFirst("C");
      
              System.out.println(deque);
          }
      }
      
      Output
      
      [C, Java, Python]



